snippet.textDisplay:
I just feel deflated. It feels the exact same as last year. Same stupid mistakes and not learning from them and changing things up. Gerrard needs to understand when subs are needed, he’s still waiting too long to make the subs when it’s obvious a change is needed 20 minutes beforehand.
Even though I understand why they had their hands up to say “ref that was a handball, goal shouldn’t have counted” - nah fuck that play to the whistle and when it goes out for a goal kick or throw in then you complain, too many times we stop playing to argue a decision when the other team keeps playing and scores from it.
6 months of hard work and grinding out results and even getting out of the group in Europe and beating them at their ground for the first time in nearly 10 years... all means virtually nothing now that we’ve messed up in January and February.
We have nothing to show for it, lost the league cup final from a goal that shouldn’t have counted but we couldn’t take our chances. Drew against Aberdeen after being denied a clear penalty and their players being allowed to elbow and suplex our players all game. Lost last night due to disgustingly poor refereeing but again we didn’t take our chances, so their bullshit goal that shouldn’t have counted and our legal goal that didn’t count means nothing. We can’t blame the refs when the team isn’t doing enough to look like they even want to win games. That’s 3 times now since we’ve came back from the winter break that we’ve been desperate for a goal in the last minutes of a game and instead of throwing everyone and everything at it, everyone running their arses off to get chances and get a goal, we pass it back and sidewards in the midfield and defence in an attempt to walk the ball into the net even though it hasn’t worked all game and the opposition has everyone behind the ball to defend a draw or a lead.

snippet.textDisplay:
Like it or not, the Taig Vermin have significantly more money, slightly better players & a stronger squad. Realistically, around 75 points pre-split was the best that could be hoped for. If the Forces of Darkness got more than that, there wasn't a realistic hope of matching them. The Spoonburners, Jambos & Killie have all been in various degrees of disarray since May, while even the Sheep have stuttered. In the early months of the season, that lot were were pish enough for Rangers to knock them over as easily as the Feenyins did. Now they're all sorting themselves to some extent, they're more likely to be sufficiently well-organised to get a result v. Rangers than v. the slightly superior Soap-dodgers.
Now need to make sure the tactical advantage of the last two Old Firm games is maintained in 4 weeks time. The result at Ibrox isn't likely to be hugely important. The result in the Scottish Cup semi or final is. Keep plugging on, but it's really a case of "Go again in July."
snippet.textOriginal:

The Spoonburners, Jambos & Killie have all been in various degrees of disarray since May, while even the Sheep have stuttered. In the early months of the season, that lot were were pish enough for Rangers to knock them over as easily as the Feenyins did. Now they're all sorting themselves to some extent, they're more likely to be sufficiently well-organised to get a result v. Rangers than v. the slightly superior Soap-dodgers. 
Now need to make sure the tactical advantage of the last two Old Firm games is maintained in 4 weeks time. The result at Ibrox isn't likely to be hugely important. The result in the Scottish Cup semi or final is. Keep plugging on, but it's really a case of "Go again in July."

snippet.textDisplay: Hopefully this proves a catalyst for Gerrard to be proactive and make some changes but I'm not sure there are many places he can go in terms of personnel. The mirroring of this time last year is startling and I think it comes down to pressure. I don't think this squad can handle it when it counts in the league. Both years having found themselves top (or effectively top thanks to a game in hand) they've had 3 weeks to think about it and everyone saying maybe this is the year. They come back and can barely do the basics. At the tail end of last season, when rangers found that new formation and played some good football, it's interesting to note that was when the pressure had lifted due to the title being out of reach. The offensive players just aren't doing it, I'm particularly annoyed with Kent and Morelos. Morelos couldn't even do the basics last night and that dive, I was raging with him and it's nights like that that show why no-one has come in for him. The comparison with Celtic's fluid formation is a good one, Rangers look over-coached and predictable. I think ultimately it's all about bottle, and I don't think they have it for a sustained push.

snippet.textDisplay: Had it coming, players have been fucking awful and we've just been getting lucky with some results. Every centre back seems to be getting dropped except from Goldson when he's the main problem, McGregors starting to get worse and the whole front three were non existent. Gerrard as per usual waiting far too long to bring on his subs to the point where its pointless even bringing them on but the person who had the worst performance on the pitch was the ref. Very inconsistent and there goal should never have stood. Apart from that we don't seem to have players who can kill a game anymore, absolutely no fucking bottle at all. Starting to think it's Gerrard who needs a kick up the arse too because it's not only the players who are underperforming. Hagi will be buzzing its only a loan deal. Leagues over, again.
